com.siemens.scp.standardbom

Class BomEntrySortComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siemens.scp.standardbom.BomEntrySortComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparator<BomEntry>

    public class BomEntrySortComparator
extends Object
implements Comparator<BomEntry>, Serializable
    Define an order on BOM entries, for sorting a given set of BOM entries. This order is not valid for finding duplicates, only for sorting.

    If any objects or values are null, they are put at the end (nulls last).

    Elements are sorted by:
    1. type
    2. group
    3. name
    4. filename
    5. version
    6. SHA1

    If elements are still equal after that, they are finally sorted by the system hash code in the current JVM. This is mostly useful for unit testing.
